<hl>
<seg id=1> The retail index in August dropped by 8.3% compared with last year. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> The retail index in August dropped by 8.3% compared with last year, and it's the twelfth month that the index has fallen continually. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Since September 1997, the retail index has been always lower than the last year, which shows that local retail businesses are still struggling at low ebb. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Compared with this July, the retail index also dropped by 8.3%. </seg>
<seg id=5> The index dropped by 3.9% excluding auto sales. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to the figure from the Department of Statistics, almost all the retail activities in August were slack. </seg>
<seg id=7> The auto sales had a big increase of 41.4% in July, but it dropped by 19.9% in August. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Other businesses whose retail sales dropped included: furniture and household wares (8%), textile and personal products (7.8%), department stores and supermarkets (2.6%), gas stations (1.3%), and groceries (0.3%). </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> On the other hand, the food index in August dropped by 4.5% compared with last year, and this has been the seventh month drop since February 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> But compared with July, the food index had increased a little bit by 1.4%. </seg>
<seg id=11> People's expenditure on food and drinks increased from 245 million to 248 million Yuan in July. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> The increase was because the turnover of snack stores increased by 6.6%. </seg>
<seg id=13> Besides restaurants, the business of other food stores increased by 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> The retail index and the food index were given by the Department of Statistics monthly to help us know the short-term conditions of retail businesses and food businesses. </seg>
</p>
</DOC>
